GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Narrative_UserFacingVsInternalLanguageSplit> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Narrative_UserFacingVsInternalLanguageSplit> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_UserFacingVsInternalLanguageSplit> ;
    narr:childCount "5"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "d1b09a828565de86" ;
    narr:narration """This hub holds the deliberate two-layer language split: human words on the user-facing surface, engineering metaphor underneath. The surface thesis is that the [full tool surface reads as plain speech](narr:Claim_FullToolSurfaceHumanWords) — perspective, cite, remember, forget, review, introspect, share — and that [the naming IS the GitHub abstraction completing](narr:Claim_GitHubAbstractionComplete): Free/Expert users never see 'compile from repo' or 'load from share bundle'. Yet the split is principled, not erasure: on the code side [the 'compile' term is retained](narr:Claim_InternalCompileTermCorrect) because the n8n workflow literally compiles memories plus transactions into a worldview snapshot. The same surface-vs-internal logic drives two later refinements (Mar 2026): with 'consult' no longer a tool name, [the word was freed](narr:Claim_ConsultTermFreed) and dropped from glossary guidance, and [the user-facing parameter was renamed](narr:Claim_IDParamRename) from perspective='share-id' to a generic id='share-id', while the proxy still strips it before forwarding. The framing was set Jul 2025 and has been firming through Mar 2026 as naming decisions land against it.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ConsultTermFreed> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_FullToolSurfaceHumanWords> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_GitHubAbstractionComplete> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_IDParamRename> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_InternalCompileTermCorrect> ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Every tool name is a word a non-technical person would use in conversation." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_FullToolSurfaceHumanWords> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "The abstraction is complete when the language doesn't leak implementation." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_GitHubAbstractionComplete> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "The engineering metaphor is correct for the engineering layer." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_InternalCompileTermCorrect> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "The word is no longer reserved terminology." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ConsultTermFreed> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "perspective(id='acupuncture-an early prospect-gotham-an engineering manager at the customer-f50e')" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_IDParamRename> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The split is not 'hide all implementation' — 'compile' is deliberately kept on the code side where the engineering metaphor is literally accurate, against the surface rule that language must not leak implementation." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_InternalCompileTermCorrect> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_GitHubAbstractionComplete> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The Jul 2025 framing is principle; the Mar 2026 children are downstream applications (consult freed, id param rename) — read them as consequences, not restatements, of the split." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ConsultTermFreed> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_IDParamRename> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The id-param rename goes further than hiding implementation: it drops the domain word 'perspective' as the parameter name in favor of a generic 'id', a tension with making every surface term a meaningful human word." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_IDParamRename> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_FullToolSurfaceHumanWords> ] ;
    narr:writer "claude (subscription)" .
}